  "texts": [
    "Note that only momenta p, p ′ that differ from each other by some moiré RLV can hybridize within the BM model.",
    "To numerically solve the continuum model, it is necessary to impose an ultraviolet cutoff.",
    "The choice of cutoff should be consistent with the symmetry of the Hamiltonian.",
    "One simple choice is a circular cutoff 7, i.e.",
    "only retaining plane wave states with|p -τ K 1 | < Λ for layer 1, and(7)|p -τ K 2 | < Λ for layer 2, (8)where the cutoff wavevector Λ satisfies k θ ≪ Λ < k D. τ = ± is a valley index corresponding to K or K ′, respectively, and its appearance in the constraints above correctly filters the plane waves into the corresponding valleys.After diagonalizing the Hamiltonian in the plane wave basis, we obtain the moiré band structure ϵ SP τ a (p) and moiré Bloch wavefunctions|ψ τ a (p)⟩ = G,l,σ u τ a;lσ (p, G) |p + G, lσ⟩,(9)where G runs over the moiré reciprocal lattice."
